##Video diary from an epidemic area (3) : 4 Stories of leaving home and returning home

Micro-signal Zairenjian11

Features, with a calm narrative against the cold | phoenix network produced in the human studio

Phoenix News Client, produced by Phoenix Network Studio on Earth

From Toronto to Wuhan, from Wuhan to Ruzhou, from Suizhou to Haikou, from Fuqing to Quanzhou... This issue's four stories relate to four journeys away or back home. The current outbreak, long or short return journey, has become complicated. Some have spent dozens of hours returning from Canada to Wuhan, others are still quarantined in hotels, still others have returned home..

1/4
On January 23, I traveled back to Wuhan from Toronto
To be together, not just to be together

January 29,2020
@ Ji Shi Yun Nina
COORDINATES: Wuhan

I am a native of Wuhan, until the age of 18, after studying abroad before long-term living in Toronto, Canada.

Right now, I'm in Wuhan.

Last October, I booked a flight back to Wuhan for the Spring Festival. Of all the days, I chose January 23rd. On This Day, received Wuhan "closed city" News, many friends also said, or cancel the trip, the risk is too big..

Perhaps for others, Wuhan is the most dangerous disaster area, is the Dragon Pool Tiger Den, but for me, there is the most safe and warm home! I prayed to God to pave the way for me if I could go back. If this is not to your liking, then block my way. After I prayed, my heart was filled with peace.

After arriving at Toronto Airport, the Cathay Pacific Counter check-in crew heard that I was going to fly to Wuhan and called the manager. The manager said, "you'd better not go back. We'll have to fly you to Hong Kong. ". And we have been informed that from the 24th, flights from Hong Kong to Wuhan will be canceled, you need to arrange your own transportation. If you have to go back, you have to sign a waiver, it was a blank, and there was only one thought, and there was always a way back.

After landing in Hong Kong, I went back and forth to six airlines with three large boxes and was told that they were either cancelled or full... The high-speed railway to Wuhan has also been suspended .... Finally, I chose to take a business charter to Shenzhen Yan sister home, and godmother together to eat the Lunar New Year reunion dinner, and then from Shenzhen back to Wuhan by train.

■ On the left is me, and on the right is my dear sister Yan. This is a rare photo of the 30th anniversary of the 2020s.

Fortunately, I got the last train ticket back to Wuhan. I had never seen a train so empty. I was the only one in the whole carriage. Train attendants came to say happy New Year, this is their last train, the beginning of the New Year morning, only to send medical and rescue related personnel. When we got to Changsha, we had a friend who had just flown back from abroad and was going back to Hubei. We all joked that it was the hardest way home ever.

I was careful to wear an N95 mask and wash my hands all the time on planes and trains. I really appreciate all the good people who helped me push the boxes along the way. They weigh 56 kilograms, which is heavier than me.

On the day I arrived home, traffic across the river was restricted in Wuhan, and some of the traffic between the 13 districts was also restricted. I came home at the last minute.

Wuhan too early, arrange!

In 10 years abroad, this is the first time I stayed at home in Wuhan for such a long time, my mother every day to change the variety of delicious Hubei home cooking. Although the city closed without freedom, but the love of my family, from all over the world friends care, let me feel that this year has been quite happy.

My aunt and uncle will be hospitalized, but we are very optimistic. So much information about the funeral, I would like to speak on behalf of some people in Wuhan who are not sick and are staying at home to tell you that we are all right. When the vacation is over, if the closures continue, I'll be working from home, and the graduate program will continue. It's nice to have a little more time at home, spend time with the family.
Chimonanthus Praecox, whose father had nurtured her for ten years, opened up again, smelling sweet and refreshing. Plum blossom is the city flower of Wuhan, a symbol of the city in the face of Challenges Aoshuang fighting Snow Spirit. Aloof one knows they aren't the snow,.

2/4
I was lucky enough to switch to the bullet train instead of riding with the passengers of the "new crown" 
But not the neighborhood

February 4,2020
@ Lin Tsun Po | ordinary citizens
Coordinates: Quanzhou, Fujian

In my impression, my mother is a strong character, do things neatly, no matter what we encounter all rush in front of the people. However, in January 2020, a silent outbreak of the coronavirus epidemic, let me find that the original mother is an old "coward. ".

January 21, roommate gets married. I planned to attend a wedding reception in Fuqing, Fujian Province, and catch a train back to Quanzhou that night for work the next day. I bought the 21:00 bullet train ticket, because I do not know the place, afraid to catch up, I changed to 21:39 tickets. At the time, Fujian was at peace with itself and there was no tension over the outbreak.

When I got home, it was quiet. On January 23, the outbreak erupted like a volcano, but I felt farther from the center of the storm. On the evening of February 1, I suddenly received a series of phone calls from the town police station, the Health Center, the neighborhood committee, and the property. They suspected that I was a close contact person with coronavirus patients, and told me to pack up my daily necessities quickly, 120's on its way to the compound. At one point I was confused and asked why they thought I was a close contact, but everyone said they were only in charge of informing, not specifically.

My mother and father began to scramble, walking around, sighing, unable to eat. I panic, but still comfort them: if I really contact with infected patients, it is good to go out quarantine, in case of infection, but also timely treatment. I walked downstairs with a change of clothes and sat down on the 120.

When I got to the isolation observation point, I found that every doctor was dressed like a beetle, the smell of disinfectant was strong, the atmosphere suddenly condensed, and my heart sank with it. They put me on the 10th floor, and I kept asking the paramedics why I was being quarantined. They called and told me: You were on the D * * * Train at 21:00 p.m. on January 21st, and there was a coronavirus infection in carriage 5.

I remember very well, Lady Luck was on my side, and that night I booked the 21:39! I excitedly "clear" myself, while trembling to open the mobile phone inside the change record, while taking out an identity card to prove their "innocence. After confirmation, I was released.

On the way home, I excitedly told my parents how good luck I had, fortunately is changed. But back in the neighborhood, a lot of people are already talking about the fact that I was just taken away. Before, my mother was afraid of being infected with the virus. She had never taken a walk in the neighborhood since the new year, but on this day, she actually said to me, let's take a walk downstairs and then go back. I know she wanted people to see that I wasn't quarantined. After the walk back home, a table of food did not move, are cold. My Mom said, we're old, we're useless, we can't afford to be scared, and if you're really isolated, your dad and I won't be able to eat or sleep. She was yelling about the whole family going back to the country, and she couldn't sleep all night. I know. She's scared.

■ This is the downstairs of my neighborhood.

I thought it was all over.

On February 3, just after 8 pm, suddenly a lot of neighbors sent wechat and called to ask: I heard that you are a close contact with patients infected with coronavirus, are you okay? The community owners exploded. My personal information is put in the Group: Name, ID number, specific address and so on. Everyone questions: My God, since the community has a person sick, how did the property did not say; this family has not come down to wander, have contact with others; good terrible! She has not isolated, but do not harm people, there is no one a unit, quickly secretly to see..

The document, like a nude photo, drew onlookers and "mobs. ". At that time I was angry to shiver all over, why my information will be sent to each community? Even if I was on a train with a patient, wouldn't my most basic information be respected? Why do people hurt me with questions? I am the "victim" , not the "culprit" .

Once again, my mother was terrified. She couldn't read or hear what was going on in the neighborhood, but from the tone of my phone call, there was a storm of gossip. I told everyone in the group, that night I have changed, did not take this train, and will change the information to the group.

I called the police station I contacted a staff member, ask why to disclose my personal information, he said not clear, but will immediately contact the property and related personnel. A few of the owners who forward my information, received a phone call from the police station, explained in the group is also for the sake of the whole community, there is no malice.

My mom called everyone she knew, explaining it was just a misunderstanding. She even felt that she was getting old, unable to keep up with the Internet age, a kind of anxiety beyond her ability. That night, she couldn't sleep again.

My case is a small part of the story, but it still affects my family's life. Think of the people of Wuhan, think of the people of Hubei, how much risk they bear, and how much pressure from all sides of public opinion.

Please in the phone or computer in front of your kind, to reduce the police pressure, to the community to create less panic.

3/4
On the fourth day of isolation in Haikou, the heart went from rejection to gratitude

January 31,2020
A native of Hubei Province who lives in Haikou
COORDINATES: A hotel in Haikou

I am from Hubei and my family has lived in Haikou for more than 5 years. On January 22, we returned to Hubei for the Spring Festival, but things took a turn for the worse. After three days at home, we took a private car and flew back to Haikou from Guilin on the 26th, before the road closure in Suizhou.

Now, it's Day four of my quarantine with my wife at a hotel near Haikou airport. Listening to the roar of the plane every day, I started from the instinct of resistance, to try to adapt, to now calmly analysis of writing. In the hope of a special period, my personal experience, written down in words.

On the night of January 26, we arrived at Guilin Airport. All Normal Airport, and did not say on the Internet will be directly persuaded to return to Hubei passengers. We had only about 30 passengers on board, and at 0.30 we arrived at the Haikou Meilan International Airport.

A temporary checkpoint has been set up at the arrival hall exit of Meilan Airport. All passengers are required to check their identity cards. If the ID card begins with 42 or Hubei Hukou, you will register and then take your temperature at a nearby focus point and fill in your personal information. Finally three or five people make up a wave, take a bus transformed by the general public (has been sterilized, the driver has done protection) to the hotel.

The airport took us to the hotel due to poor operation management, but the hotel was fully occupied and there were no transfer orders. By the time the Meilan District government leaders came in the middle of the night, we had been waiting in the cold wind for more than two hours.
After leadership coordination, we were temporarily placed at the Haikou Farmer Training Center by the sea. The accommodations were poor, with no breakfast in the morning and only people re-registering to take their temperature. Until around 10:30, a 13-seater arrived and crammed 12 of us into it. I was a little distracted.

This time, we moved to a slightly Nicer Hotel, where we took our temperature, checked in, checked in. From midnight until a little after 11 am the next day, we had nothing to eat and were famished. As a young man, I felt fine, but there were old people and children among the 12. There's a lot of grumbling going on. It happens.

Our hotel has a total of 68 rooms, as of the evening of the 29th, a total of 82 Hubei residents. The hotel has about 24 staff members from the local agricultural bureau, the town government, the health department, the Public Security Bureau, the joint defense and other departments, as well as some volunteers. According to on-site functions, it is divided into the medical group, Publicity Group, Logistics Support Group, Security Group. My husband and I live in a room, more than 50 square meters, when entering the door has a very strong smell of disinfectant.

Here, we had our first lunch, white cut chicken and lettuce, the meal was perfect, the dinner was beef and a vegetable. The second day of breakfast is two steamed stuffed bun, eggs and a soy milk, the third and fourth day of breakfast is two bread and eggs, soy milk. Starting the next day, lunch was a mixture of two meat dishes, plus one vegetarian dish.

As a new Hainanese from Hubei Province, when he first encountered this kind of "special treatment" , he still had some instinct to reject it. However, we can also understand and support these exceptional initiatives. City, district leaders, field staff are actually quite hard, empathy, we also feel that to give others trouble. We had regular, relatively good meals, free masks, warm service, two daily temperature checks... the initial period of isolation, the staff lack of protective equipment, many people are only wearing a one-time raincoat.
Staff Line up outside the hotel window.

How are we going to get through this? Luckily, I had a cell phone, good Wi-fi, and I could read, and yesterday I jogged around my room for 30 minutes. Although can not go out, but also is fighting with the people of the whole country new coronary pneumonia.

On February 2, we moved to a nearby four-star Standard Hotel. The service is better now, and the staff is getting better equipped. From the bottom of my heart, I would like to thank Haikou for their hard work and service during this special period. Finally want to say a familiar words, "today's inconvenience, is for the future better unblocked. ".

4/4

After the 14-day incubation period, I had a sense of unbinding

February 2,2020
@ Feng Jing | graduate student, Wuhan University
Coordinates: Ruzhou, Henan Province

20200202 is said to be the "symmetry day of the Millennium. " . For me, today is my 14th day back home from Wuhan. The incubation period of "new coronavirus" is 14 days, at this moment I have a feeling of unsealing.

My hometown is in Henan Ruzhou, I am studying graduate school in Wuhan. My own experience these days is a bit of a "magical reality" , so write it down.

In early January, I saw on Weibo, "Wuhan appeared unknown virus" , "Wuhan South China Seafood Game, " and other hot search, but because every day to prepare classes, classes, and activities in the school, there is not too much attention. It wasn't until mid-january, when my family called to check on my health, that I realized the problem, but didn't take it too seriously, reassuring them: "It's not as scary as it sounds on the Internet. We're all fine. "

On January 20, I packed my bags and prepared to go home. After I arrived in Zhengzhou, I made an appointment to see a good friend, when she came to see me, she joked, "because you are from Wuhan, I want to buy a mask to put on. " I also joked: "fireproof, anti-theft and anti-virus. " Wearing a mask to chat for a while, wish each other a happy new year, happy wave goodbye.

There was a lot of traffic at the Zhengzhou Railway Station, but not a lot of people were wearing masks. My father came to the station to meet me and asked the situation in Wuhan. Along the way, airports, stations, subways, buses, shopping malls, supermarkets, business as usual. To be on the safe side, I took my temperature, which was a little over 36 degrees, normal, and my family didn't ask any more questions.

To avoid suspicion, I did not go out on the 21st and 22nd, three times a day temperature, all showed normal. After that, I was relieved to walk in the community, but also to visit my aunt in the next community. My uncle's family is a doctor. My aunt paid special attention and advised me: "stay at home for a long time this time, go to school later. The epidemic in Wuhan should be quite serious. Protect Yourself! " In order to make my aunt feel at ease, I promised to say yes, but thinking "June graduation, thesis, defense, work... really should not stay at home too long Ah! "

Early on the morning of the 23rd, my aunt called and said, "the city of Wuhan is closed! It's really serious! You need to take it seriously! " My first reaction was not to be glad I left Wuhan, but to have a feeling of wanting to go back and carry it with me.

Just hang up aunt's phone, Dad's phone rang, is the leader of their unit, said someone reported me from Wuhan Back, want to confirm. Dad answered truthfully and said he would cooperate if necessary. My sister was terrified. She was afraid I'd be taken away in quarantine. After hanging up the phone, my parents told me: "To be safe, you do not go out to find classmates, at home to read a book is good. " Special period, but also for the safety of others to understand each other. But it's still weird to be reported.

May Be at home for a long time, everyone will feel bored, students become active. We shared hard-core slogans and videos from our neighborhood, and we were so happy to be "so well protected" that we temporarily forgot about the severity of the outbreak. My friends and relatives and the end of each chat also became "safe and sound. ". Soon, the Internet frequently reposted Henan "hard nuclear protection means. ". "Henan Province is so powerful! " Wrote Netizens. "Ask for a Governor of Henan! " "The people of Henan Province are so protective! " . Those of us who have been the most notorious users of the region, because of an epidemic has been inexplicably exaggerated talk up, it is a little bit uncomfortable.

A city that has been through countless wars in its history, a city that has provided a safe haven for tens of millions of people, and a place for students from all over the world to learn and think, the city, which hosted the military games last October, is now under fire and abuse. Perhaps because he is Henan people, experienced by the black was random abuse, so know this "to add to the crime" of helplessness.

In order to avoid suspicion, I will not go out during the day, eight or nine in the evening community after no one put on a mask to take a walk downstairs. Who knows the next day or dad received a call from work, to statistics of my school, school number, ID number and which train to take back. Even someone reported me to go out activities, my father unit directly sent a staff member to my door guard. After hearing this, my sister said bluntly: "This is not spying! " My father said: "Now is a special period, understand it. "

Chatting with my grandfather in the evening, I said: "always at home, feeling a bit boring. " My grandfather replied: "You just a few days, you feel boring! I have almost twenty-four years. " We smiled at each other. GRANDPA had a disease more than twenty years ago, and he was unable to move. He just stayed at home or walked on the balcony every day. When I was a child, I always felt that my grandfather was very tall. Now his back is bent like a shrimp. Sometimes he watches TV and falls asleep looking at it, even when he is sunning himself on the balcony. One Minute he is talking to you and the next he falls asleep. GRANDPA's getting old. What does he think about when he can't sleep?

The 24th, New Year's Eve, according to the custom of the north, this day should be kept. But in order to improve immunity, family members are tacit understanding to go to bed early, the Spring Festival evening did not see much, and friends between the New Year blessings have become "peace and security. ". Before going to bed, my sister specially came to my room and said: "sister, we had a very special Spring Festival! "

On the 26th, a classmate in the class group suddenly sent a message saying: "If there is a strange number to call you, students do not answer! " Asked the reason, only to know that many students phone, ID card information was leaked. Another student said, be careful about strangers adding to your wechat account, several strangers adding to him..

Aunt said that our city's medical staff, this day began all staff on duty, formal training, ready to support Wuhan. We were silent for a long time. As family members, we knew too much about the responsibilities of the PROFESSION IN TIMES OF CRISIS! All we can do is pray for their safety and protect ourselves "from trouble" .

The world is fickle, like a reed.

On the 31st, we found an infected person in our city, and everything went to Hell. My parents'phones rang again, all to check on my health. Half an hour later, medical staff wearing thick protective clothing to my home temperature measurement. For Safety, the whole family measured. Every day, morning and night. It's better that way. We're both safe.

I got home on the 20th, February 2nd, 2020, exactly 14 days. Now, my family and I are safe, as are the friends and family I came into contact with. The two of US joked: "This is the life of the friendship! "

Reading, eating, doing exercises, playing mobile phones, the day will be over. The following day will continue to actively cooperate with the staff temperature, I hope the family safe! Every night before going to bed, I would pray for the epidemic to pass quickly, I strongly hope to go back to Wuhan!

My hometown is in Henan Ruzhou, I am studying graduate school in Wuhan. My own experience these days is a bit of a "magical reality" , so write it down.

We're all fine. "

On January 20, I packed my bags and prepared to go home. After I arrived in Zhengzhou, I made an appointment to see a good friend, when she came to see me, she joked, "because you are from Wuhan, I want to buy a mask to put on. " I also joked: "fireproof, anti-theft and anti-virus. " Wearing a mask to chat for a while, wish each other a happy new year, happy wave goodbye.

There was a lot of traffic at the Zhengzhou Railway Station, but not a lot of people were wearing masks. My father came to the station to meet me and asked the situation in Wuhan. Along the way, airports, stations, subways, buses, shopping malls, supermarkets, business as usual. To be on the safe side, I took my temperature, which was a little over 36 degrees, normal, and my family didn't ask any more questions.

To avoid suspicion, I did not go out on the 21st and 22nd, three times a day temperature, all showed normal. Just hang up aunt's phone, Dad's phone rang, is the leader of their unit, said someone reported me from Wuhan Back, want to confirm. Dad answered truthfully and said he would cooperate if necessary. My sister was terrified. She was afraid I'd be taken away in quarantine. After hanging up the phone, my parents told me: "To be safe, you do not go out to find classmates, at home to read a book is good. " Special period, but also for the safety of others to understand each other. But it's still weird to be reported.

" Wrote Netizens. "Ask for a Governor of Henan! " "The people of Henan Province are so protective! " . " My father said: "Now is a special period, understand it. "

" We smiled at each other. GRANDPA had a disease more than twenty years ago, and he was unable to move. He just stayed at home or walked on the balcony every day. When I was a child, I always felt that my grandfather was very tall. Now his back is bent like a shrimp. Sometimes he watches TV and falls asleep looking at it, even when he is sunning himself on the balcony. One Minute he is talking to you and the next he falls asleep. GRANDPA's getting old. What does he think about when he can't sleep?

The 24th, New Year's Eve, according to the custom of the north, this day should be kept. ". Before going to bed, my sister specially came to my room and said: "sister, we had a very special Spring Festival! "

As family members, we knew too much about the responsibilities of the PROFESSION IN TIMES OF CRISIS! All we can do is pray for their safety and protect ourselves "from trouble" .

The world is fickle, like a reed.

As family members, we knew too much about the responsibilities of the PROFESSION IN TIMES OF CRISIS! All we can do is pray for their safety and protect ourselves "from trouble" .

The world is fickle, like a reed.

On the 31st, we found an infected person in our city, and everything went to Hell. My parents'phones rang again, all to check on my health. Half an hour later, medical staff wearing thick protective clothing to my home temperature measurement. For Safety, the whole family measured. Every day, morning and night. It's better that way. We're both safe.

I got home on the 20th, February 2nd, 2020, exactly 14 days. Now, my family and I are safe, as are the friends and family I came into contact with. The two of US joked: "This is the life of the friendship! "

Reading, eating, doing exercises, playing mobile phones, the day will be over. The following day will continue to actively cooperate with the staff temperature, I hope the family safe! Every night before going to bed, I would pray for the epidemic to pass quickly, I strongly hope to go back to Wuhan!

Wuhan! GET WELL SOON!
